CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 15, 1955, pg. 1 reads: "Witness From New Jersey - Miss Nettie Horne, who in 1950 moved to Newark, N.J., told the U.S. Federal Court at the vote fraud trials that she did not vote in New Kensington during the 1952 election. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Double exposure: Witness Nettie Horne wearing light colored straw hat and striped long sleeved blouse, standing by desk with sign reading "Witness for United States Report at Desk," in Allegheny County Courthouse for vote fraud trial; Overhead light fixture with patterned glass shade
